Problem Understanding

You are given:

A string containing uppercase letters.
A number k.

You can change at most k characters.

Example 1
s = "XYYX"
k = 2

Can we make the whole string same?

Yes.

Option 1:

X Y Y X
↓     ↓
Y Y Y Y

Replace both X → Y

Used replacements = 2

Length = 4

So answer is 4.




Solution 1:
class Solution {
    fun characterReplacement(s: String, k: Int): Int {
        val map = mutableMapOf<Char,Int>()
        var left = 0
        var maxFreq = 0
        var result = 0

        for(right in s.indices){
            // store frequency
            map[s[right]] = map.getOrDefault(s[right],0) + 1 
            // get max frequency
            maxFreq = maxOf(maxFreq,map[s[right]]!!)
            // window size
            var windowSize = right - left + 1

            while(windowSize - maxFreq > k){
                map[s[left]] = map.getOrDefault(s[left],0) - 1
                left++
                windowSize = right - left + 1
            }
            result = maxOf(result,windowSize)
        }

        return result
    }
}



Solution 2:
class Solution {
    fun characterReplacement(s: String, k: Int): Int {
        var i = 0
        var maxFreq = 0
        var maxlen = 0
        val freq = IntArray(26)

        for(j in s.indices){
            // store the frequency of new character
            val index = s[j] - 'A'
            freq[index]++
            // store the maximum freq of new character
            maxFreq = maxOf(maxFreq,freq[index])
            // window size
            val windowSize = j - i + 1
            /*
                1. check the replacement required
                replacement = windowSize - maxFrequency
                2. if replacement is greater thean "K" then shrink window
             */
            if(windowSize - maxFreq > k){
                freq[s[i] - 'A']--
                i++
            }
            // shore the max length of the window
            maxlen = maxOf(maxlen,(j-i+1))
        }
        return maxlen
    }
}
